seal               : You are not one self but an ecosystem — a hundred trillion microbes in your gut that help digest your food, train your immune system, and, through the vagus nerve and a traffic of molecules, sway your mood, stress, and cravings. A mind shaped, in part, by a council of bacteria with no mind at all.
